  "bio_raw": "Dr. Irfanullah is a visiting research fellow of the Center for Sustainable Development (CSD) of the ULAB. Over the past 25 years, he has evolved from being an algal taxonomist to an aquatic ecologist, from a conservationist to a development facilitator. At the current stage of his evolution, he finds his niche in nature-people-knowledge nexus. Over these years, he has developed interest in and understanding of nature-based solutions, environmental governance, climate change adaptation, technology for poverty alleviation, scholarly communication, and research impact — all focusing on human well-being.\nDr. Irfanullah has worked for and has been associated with different national and international environmental, development, learned, and research organisations. He is also associated with many peer-reviewed journals, learned societies, funding agencies, and knowledge and professional networks. He helps his organisations with strategic direction and expert opinion; influencing policy and practice; planning, managing and ensuring quality of programmes; and fundraising and financial management.\nDr. Irfanullah brings in expertise in creating, capturing and communicating knowledge; testing and promoting new ideas; and facilitating collaboration and network. He and his co-workers have so far published 49 journal articles; have authored, edited and contributed to more than 55 books and other publications; and have written about 215 articles and thought pieces on diverse topics — from freshwater ecosystems to climate change adaptation to poverty-technology link to wildlife conservation to research system. As a research enthusiast, he often works with researchers, journal editors, and pertinent national and international agencies for improving research system.",
  "stated_interests": [],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD in Biological Sciences (Aquatic Ecology);\n2004; the University of Liverpool, UK.\nMSc in Botany (with thesis in Hydrobiology);\n1995 (result in 1999); University of Dhaka; 1st class (1st position).\nBSc in Botany (with Honours);\n1994 (result in 1997); University of Dhaka; 1st class (1st position)."
    }
